ton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qcz1665702682393.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qcz1665702682393.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qcz1665702682393.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qcz1665702682393\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__uputames_408408\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Put an asynchronous message in the input queue of the calling application.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__topic_d123587e1_d123588e1_d123589e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104qcz1665702682393_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__codeblock_qwv_sdk_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">short uputames (unsigned char*message, longlength);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__topic_d87332e1_d87333e1_d87334e1_d87335e1_d87336e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422930e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__parml_d4h_5dk_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">message</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Message data to send</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">length</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Size of the message data</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__note_N10058_N1002F_N10016_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The maximum length of a message is 255 bytes.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__topic_d87337e1_d87338e1_d87339e1_d87340e1_d87341e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422930e93\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__p_d123599e1_d123600e1_d123601e1\">0—<code class=\"ph codeph\">uputames</code> always returns\n            zero.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__topic_d87342e1_d87343e1_d87344e1_d87345e1_d87346e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422930e105\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__topic_d87347e1_d87348e1_d87349e1_d87350e1_d87351e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422930e118\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__p_d123611e1_d123612e1_d123613e1\"><span class=\"keyword apiname\">uputames</span> places an asynchronous\n            message, containing the specified data, in the input queue of the calling application.\n            If the calling application has code in the receiveMessage trigger, either in the\n            application shell or in the active form, that trigger will be activated, and the data is\n            passed to it in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>, as soon as the application is idle, that is,\n            when it is not reading user input or processing ProcScript. Because it can never be\n            guaranteed that the application will process the message, we refrain from using the term\n            ‘sending a message’. All this routine does is put the message in a queue. If the\n            application has no code in a receiveMessage trigger anywhere, the message will never be\n            seen.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__p_d123614e1_d123615e1_d123616e1\">Uniface removes any non-printable characters (ASCII\n            value less than 32 or greater than 127) before placing the received message in\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>. This is done because these characters have special\n            meaning in Uniface, and are not generally usable, or even desirable, in ProcScript. A\n            message containing non-printable characters should be processed in 3GL code. For this\n            purpose, the service routine <span class=\"keyword apiname\">ugetames</span> provides the message in its\n            original, unfiltered format.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__p_d123617e1_d123618e1_d123619e1\"><span class=\"keyword apiname\">uputames</span> cannot be used to send\n            an asynchronous message to another application.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__section_tpf_zdk_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d422930e146\">Example:  uputames</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example sends data in a C structure. Because of the way the\n            structure members are filled, using <span class=\"keyword apiname\">strcpy</span>, the structure contains\n            non-printable characters (the zero terminators of the strings). However, these are not\n            transmitted to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>, as the resulting output shows.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104qcz1665702682393_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__codeblock_xvs_12k_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;string.h&gt;\n\nEXPORT void send_code_and_description ()\n{\nstruct\n{\nchar code[6];\nchar desc[6];\n} data;\n\nstrcpy(data.code, \"123\");\nstrcpy(data.desc, \"Desc\");\n\n(void)uputames((unsigned char *)&amp;data, sizeof(data));\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The receiveMessage trigger contains this code:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104qcz1665702682393_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__codeblock_lkz_c2k_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">message/info \"ASYNC&gt; Got async message:[%%$result]\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The output from the receiveMessage trigger is:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104qcz1665702682393_html_3\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"qcz1665702682393__codeblock_dyv_22k_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">ASYNC&gt; Got async message:[123Desc</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mjf1665702682527.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetames</a><p>Get the complete, unfiltered asynchronous message from the input queue.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531200\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uputames Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Put an asynchronous message in the input queue of the calling application. Explain this code short uputames (unsigned char*message, longlength); Copy Parameters message Message data to send length Size of the message data Note: The maximum length of a message is 255 bytes. Return Values 0— uputames always returns zero. Use Library: yrtl Description uputames places an asynchronous message, containing the specified data, in the input queue of the calling application. If the calling application has code in the receiveMessage trigger, either in the application shell or in the active form, that trigger will be activated, and the data is passed to it in $result , as soon as the application is idle, that is, when it is not reading user input or processing ProcScript. Because it can never be guaranteed that the application will process the message, we refrain from using the term ‘sending a message’. All this routine does is put the message in a queue. If the application has no code in a receiveMessage trigger anywhere, the message will never be seen. Uniface removes any non-printable characters (ASCII value less than 32 or greater than 127) before placing the received message in $result . This is done because these characters have special meaning in Uniface, and are not generally usable, or even desirable, in ProcScript. A message containing non-printable characters should be processed in 3GL code. For this purpose, the service routine ugetames provides the message in its original, unfiltered format. uputames cannot be used to send an asynchronous message to another application. Example: uputames The following example sends data in a C structure. Because of the way the structure members are filled, using strcpy , the structure contains non-printable characters (the zero terminators of the strings). However, these are not transmitted to $result , as the resulting output shows. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <string.h> EXPORT void send_code_and_description () { struct { char code[6]; char desc[6]; } data; strcpy(data.code, \"123\"); strcpy(data.desc, \"Desc\"); (void)uputames((unsigned char *)&data, sizeof(data)); } Copy The receiveMessage trigger contains this code: Explain this code message/info \"ASYNC> Got async message:[%%$result]\" Copy The output from the receiveMessage trigger is: Explain this code ASYNC> Got async message:[123Desc Copy Related Links ugetames Get the complete, unfiltered asynchronous message from the input queue. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}